# Theme Variable Sync

When updating `src/theme.css` or any theme-related color variables, **also update all color theme files** in `src/lib/themes/css/` with their palette-appropriate equivalents.

## Scope

- **Base theme**: `src/theme.css` (defines `:root` defaults and `prefers-color-scheme: light` overrides)
- **Color themes**: `src/lib/themes/css/*.css` (15 files: bit-classic, dracula, github-classic, macos, linear, etc.)

## Theme File Structure

Each theme file has two blocks:

| Block | Selector | Purpose |
|-------|----------|---------|
| Dark | `[data-theme="name"][data-color-mode="dark"]` | Dark mode overrides |
| Light | `[data-theme="name"][data-color-mode="light"]` | Light mode overrides |

## Variables to Keep in Sync

When you add, remove, or change any of these in `theme.css`, update all theme files:

- `--bit-rgb-*` (RGB primitives)
- `--bit-color-paper`, `--bit-color-paper-hover`, `--bit-color-paper-2`
- `--bit-color-accent-*`, `--bit-color-muted`
- `--bit-color-ink`, `--bit-color-ink-muted`
- `--bit-color-heading`, `--bit-color-avatar-outline`
- `--bit-color-inverse-*`, `--bit-color-diff-*`
- `--bit-gradient-surface`, `--bit-color-panel-bg`, `--bit-color-code-bg`

## Checklist

- [ ] Change applied to `src/theme.css` (base or `prefers-color-scheme: light`)
- [ ] All 15 theme files updated with their palette-appropriate values
- [ ] Dark mode: use theme-appropriate dark colors (e.g. `rgba(var(--bit-rgb-fg), 0.05)` for overlay hovers)
- [ ] Light mode: use theme-appropriate light colors (e.g. `#f0f0f0` for paper-hover)
